The paper presents a novel approach for parallel computation in the context of machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The approach involves a set of independent workers that use broadcast to update each other, which could also fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also applies the approach to learning boosted trees, which could suggest it belongs to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques, which could also be relevant sub-categories.
